{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idab0bbd2c-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8063"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"8063"},"text":"§ 8063.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" United States Marine Corps: composition; functions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab0bbd2d-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8063/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Marine Corps, within the Department of the Navy, shall be so organized as to include not less than three combat divisions and three air wings, and such other land combat, aviation, and other services as may be organic therein. The Marine Corps shall be organized, trained, and equipped to provide fleet marine forces of combined arms, together with supporting air components, for service with the fleet in the seizure or defense of advanced naval bases and for the conduct of such land operations as may be essential to the prosecution of a naval campaign. In addition, the Marine Corps shall provide detachments and organizations for service on armed vessels of the Navy, shall provide security detachments for the protection of naval property at naval stations and bases, and shall perform such other duties as the President may direct. However, these additional duties may not detract from or interfere with the operations for which the Marine Corps is primarily organized.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab0bbd2e-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8063/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Marine Corps shall develop, in coordination with the Army and the Air Force, those phases of amphibious operations that pertain to the tactics, technique, and equipment used by landing forces.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab0bbd2f-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s8063/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Marine Corps is responsible, in accordance with integrated joint mobilization plans, for the expansion of peacetime components of the Marine Corps to meet the needs of war.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idab0bbd30-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/278"},"text":"70A Stat. 278","children":[],"tail":", § 5013; renumbered § 5063, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/433/tV/s511/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–433, title V, § 511(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/1043"},"text":"100 Stat. 1043","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 8063, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/dA/tVIII/s807/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232, div. A, title VIII, § 807(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-08-13"},"text":"Aug. 13, 2018","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/132/1834"},"text":"132 Stat. 1834","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idab0bbd31-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idab0bbd32-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"idab0bbd33-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","at